Players take turns drawing a card from either the deck or the discard pile and then discarding one card. The first player to form a valid hand can "knock," ending the round. The knocker's deadwood (unmatched cards) must have a total value lower than that of their opponent's to score points.
incorrect answer: Oklahoma Gin is played with two decks of 52 cards each. The goal is to collect all cards of the same color. Each player is dealt 5 cards.
